replies.bodyText:
I was not able to create a cluster until tristantarrant/infinispan-playground-testdriver#3
I have fixed ContainerInfinispanServerDriver
The main changes were:

public static final String IMAGE_USER = "185";
builder.run("usermod -u " + IMAGE_USER + " jboss");
The prebuilt image has the user 185, in this case, now we are also setting the user 185

I have changed the user to 200 and also removed:
if (!prebuiltImage) {
  builder.run("usermod -u " + IMAGE_USER + " jboss");
}

It means that, if we built the image on the fly, will have a user 200
If we use a prebuilt image, we are setting the user to 200
When executing chown or chmod with an UID, Linux won't fail. ( This was a surprise for me)
I have executed the test in https://github.com/tristantarrant/infinispan-playground-testdriver and it passed.
